  <data name="Manual_Faq_Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>FAQ</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Manual_Faq_Status_Q" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Q1: How do I view job status?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Manual_Faq_Status_A" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Use Hangfire Dashboard to view job status, history, and failure details.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Manual_Faq_Failure_Q" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Q2: What happens when a job fails?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Manual_Faq_Failure_A" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Hangfire applies its configured retry policy. Failed jobs can be inspected from the Dashboard.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Manual_Faq_UpdateSchedule_Q" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Q3: How do I update a recurring schedule?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Manual_Faq_UpdateSchedule_A" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Submit the recurring action again with the same job name or job id and the new Cron expression.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Manual_Faq_Delay_Q" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Q4: Why can scheduled jobs run late?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Manual_Faq_Delay_A" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Execution can be affected by worker availability, server load, polling intervals, and storage latency.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Manual_Faq_Delete_Q" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Q5: How do I delete a recurring job?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Manual_Faq_Delete_A" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Use the Hangfire Dashboard recurring jobs page or remove the recurring job through Hangfire APIs.</value>
  </data>
